k analyzes the masu form as an index of various social identities and activities. The book discusses both socialization through speech styles and socialization to use an appropriate speech style. Qualitative analysis of dinnertime conversations demonstrates how learners are implicitly and explicitly socialized into the norms of style shift in Japanese in interaction with their host family members.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aJapanese languagexSocial aspects. 0aJapanese languagexSpoken Japanese. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Psycholinguistics.2bisacsh  aL2 Japanese.  aL2 identity.  aSLA.  aSecond Language Acquisition.  aidentity.  alanguage socialization.  alearners of Japanese as a foreign language.  asocialization.  aspeech styles.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311102473808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z97831106067130 cprintz978184769101940uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978184769102640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847691026423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847691026/original  a978-3-11-060671-3  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066313-6  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-102473-8  MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK